Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is noteworthy the variety of aquatic bird types in which HPAI H5 virus was detected; namely gull, heron, duck, tern, cormorant, and grebe.

Ubsu-Nur lake is a huge wetland that congregates a great abundance and diversity of aquatic birds. It is a stopover site for migratory birds using the central Asian flyway, which covers a large continental area of Eurasia between the Arctic Ocean and the Indian Ocean. This flyway comprises several important migration routes of waterbirds that migrate over immense distances, and therefore the finding of this HPAI H5 virus in so many species here is of concern for a vast territory.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of the affected area can be seen at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4298345,5759. - Mod.PMB]
